1930s Norris Green properties typically have heating systems installed in the 1970s or 1980s as the first upgrade from solid fuel or back boilers. These systems are now 40 to 50 years old. Pump failures, motorised valve failures and system boiler faults are common in heating systems of this age, and the issue is usually the system boiler and cylinder combination rather than the individual components that a quick fix addresses. We diagnose the root cause correctly before recommending any work. We also carry out <a href="/power-flushing-liverpool" style="color:var(--orange);font-weight:700;">power flushing</a> for L11 systems with cold radiators, <a href="/radiators-liverpool" style="color:var(--orange);font-weight:700;">radiator replacements</a> and <a href="/gas-safety-certificate-liverpool" style="color:var(--orange);font-weight:700;">gas safety certificates</a> for Norris Green landlords.</p>
